<p>The Trump administration has sent warships, fighter jets and surveillance aircraft toward Venezuelan waters in a campaign Washington describes as aimed at &#x27;narco-terrorists,&#x27; marking a notable escalation in U.S. operations in the Caribbean . The aircraft carrier USS Gerald R. Ford is moving closer to Venezuela, and President Trump warned the effort could include &quot;land action,&quot; signaling a broadening of possible options . Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro called the moves a fabricated pretext for war and said his government will avoid conflict while moving to revoke the citizenship of an opponent he accuses of encouraging an invasion . The developments raise regional tensions and have prompted Venezuelan military preparations as diplomatic concerns grow .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/zr3nJgjIfY2lNlPV1JqLoMz61GSwCXWSqvNJsfKd0WOMWt0ypfh6P6dvK4BcqJJmvOZYa7T1aMsMpl6bpPeR5Jp2EOEUIWA7sO1qNncDgWk9ueAVxkBY8bdD1-zuzvjkLW-shP9nDGeGJMBwrjWqvp9q7b4keiNoID69i4JYxrG6XKPTXajbXaW0iC7OfwuHi0chEwPBM86mw5gQ' alt='Venezuelan president Nicolás Maduro speaking as tensions with the United States escalate' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Carrier details: The USS Gerald R. Ford is described in coverage as the world&#x27;s biggest warship as it approaches the Caribbean, increasing the operation&#x27;s visibility .</li><li>Venezuelan response: Defense Minister Vladimir Padrino López said Venezuela is conducting military exercises in response to the U.S. movements .</li><li>Previous maritime actions: Recent reporting notes the U.S. has bombed 10 alleged drug-smuggling boats since Sept 2, part of its stepped-up maritime campaign .</li><li>Domestic politics: Maduro said he aims to revoke the citizenship of an opposition figure he accuses of egging on an invasion, framing the domestic move as a defensive step .</li></ul><blockquote>They promised they would never again get involved in a war, and they are fabricating a war that we will avoid - Nicolás Maduro</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>United States administration: U.S. officials describe the deployments as part of an armed campaign against &#x27;narco-terrorists&#x27; and have moved ships, fighter jets and surveillance aircraft into the region . (<a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/10/26/us-military-ships-planes-venezuela/'>Washington Post</a>)</li><li>President Trump: The President warned the campaign could expand to include &#x27;land action,&#x27; signaling a broader range of military options . (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c891gzx7xn4o'>BBC</a>)</li><li>President Nicolás Maduro: Maduro said the U.S. is &#x27;fabricating&#x27; a war and pledged to avoid armed confrontation while taking steps against an opponent he blames for incitement . (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/maduro-says-the-us-is-fabricating-a-war-and-seeks-to-revoke-citizenship-of-opponent/article70204078.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>Venezuelan defence minister: Vladimir Padrino López announced that Venezuela is carrying out military exercises as U.S. forces approach Venezuelan waters . (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/26/venezuelas-maduro-says-the-us-is-fabricating-a-war-against-him'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/10/26/us-military-ships-planes-venezuela/'>What to know about the U.S. forces closing in on Venezuela</a> - washingtonpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/maduro-says-the-us-is-fabricating-a-war-and-seeks-to-revoke-citizenship-of-opponent/article70204078.ece'>Maduro says the U.S. is fabricating a war and seeks to revoke citizenship of opponent</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/venezuelas-maduro-says-u-s-is-fabricating-a-war-as-aircraft-carrier-approaches-caribbean'>Venezuela’s Maduro says U.S. is ‘fabricating’ a war as aircraft carrier approaches Caribbean</a> - pbs.org</li><li><